        <updateDate>2020-07-02T16:43:54Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Purple Heart Flag Act</b></p> <p>This bill designates a flag as the Purple Heart Flag (which recognizes soldiers wounded during hostilities) and requires that it be displayed in a manner visible to the public.</p> <p>The Flag shall be displayed on Armed Forces Day, Memorial Day, Flag Day, National POW/MIA Recognition Day, and Veterans Day in the following locations:</p> <ul> <li>the World War II Memorial; </li> <li>the Korean War Veterans Memorial; </li> <li>the Vietnam Veterans Memorial; </li> <li>each national cemetery; </li> <li>the buildings containing the official offices of the Secretary of State, the Secretary of Defense, the Secretary of Veterans Affairs, and the Director of the Selective Service System; and </li> <li>each medical center of the Department of Veterans Affairs. </li></ul>]]></text>
      </summary>
